'''Orland Township''' is one of thirty [[Civil township|townships]] in [[Cook County, Illinois|Cook County]], [[Illinois]], [[United States|USA]].  As of the [[United States Census, 2000|2000 census]], its population was 91,418<ref>[http://factfinder.census.gov/servlet/DTTable?_bm=y&-context=dt&-ds_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U&-mt_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U_P001&-CONTEXT=dt&-tree_id=4001&-all_geo_types=N&-geo_id=06000US1703156614&-search_results=01000US&-format=&-_lang=en United States Census Bureau American FactFinder]</ref>.

==Geography==
According to the [[United States Census Bureau]], Orland Township covers an area of 36.47 square miles (94.45 square kilometers); of this, 35.74 square miles (92.55 square kilometers, 97.99 percent) is land and 0.73 square miles (1.89 square kilometers, 2 percent) is water.  It includes the entire village of [[Orland Hills, Illinois|Orland Hills]], almost all of [[Orland Park, Illinois|Orland Park]], as well as a large portion of [[Tinley Park, Illinois|Tinley Park]].

===Boundaries===
Orland Township is bordered by Harlem Avenue ([[Illinois Route 43]]) on the east, 135th Street on the north, Will-Cook Road on the west (where Cook County and Will County share a border), and 183rd Street on the south (which is also the Cook-Will county border).

===Cities, towns, villages===
* [[Orland Hills, Illinois|Orland Hills]]
* [[Orland Park, Illinois|Orland Park]]
* [[Tinley Park, Illinois|Tinley Park]]

===Adjacent townships===
* [[Palos Township, Cook County, Illinois|Palos Township]] (north)
* [[Worth Township, Cook County, Illinois|Worth Township]] (northeast)
* [[Bremen Township, Cook County, Illinois|Bremen Township]] (east)
* [[Rich Township, Cook County, Illinois|Rich Township]] (southeast)
* [[Frankfort Township, Will County, Illinois|Frankfort Township, Will County]] (south)
* [[New Lenox Township, Will County, Illinois|New Lenox Township, Will County]] (southwest)
* [[Homer Township, Will County, Illinois|Homer Township, Will County]] (west)
* [[Lemont Township, Cook County, Illinois|Lemont Township]] (northwest)

===Cemeteries===
The township contains these four cemeteries: Cooper, German Methodist, Old German Methodist and Orland Park.

